The Deputy President has indicated that the Jubilee Party will beat the National Super Alliance (NASA) in the repeat presidential poll slated for October 26.
 DP Ruto stressed that President Uhuru Kenyatta will trounce Opposition leader, Raila Odinga, like he did in the August 8 General Election. 
 ALSO READ:

NASA: The only language Jubilee Government understands is mass action

 He dismissed NASA’s call for election boycott, pointing out that Jubilee is ready for the showdown as the Constitution dictates.
 Ruto, however, stated that the Jubilee brigade must address electoral laws and other major reforms before the poll as directed by the Supreme Court.




(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});

 “The Supreme Court said the systems had issues and the only way to change them is through a change of laws. Agwambo (Raila Odinga) himself has said ‘no reforms, no elections’ and that is why we need to do the reforms in Parliament,” he said.
 
 
